  "prompt": "After demonetization, which could be next step that needs to be taken by Indian Government to prevent black money and corruption?",
  "response": "After demonetization, the Indian government can consider several steps to prevent black money and corruption:\n\n1. Digital Financial Transactions\n- Promote digital payment systems\n- Incentivize digital transactions\n- Reduce cash transactions\n- Implement lower transaction fees for digital payments\n\n2. Strengthen Legal Framework\n- Implement stricter anti-corruption laws\n- Enhance Lokpal and Lokayukta mechanisms\n- Strengthen prosecution systems\n- Create faster judicial processes for corruption cases\n\n3. Tax Reforms\n- Simplify tax procedures\n- Lower tax rates\n- Implement comprehensive GST\n- Improve tax compliance mechanisms\n- Introduce advanced technology for tax monitoring\n\n4. Enhanced Surveillance\n- Use advanced technologies for financial tracking\n- Implement sophisticated data analytics\n- Create robust financial intelligence units\n- Improve information sharing between agencies\n\n5. Transparency Measures\n- Implement blockchain technology\n- Introduce digital audit trails\n- Mandate online financial disclosures\n- Develop comprehensive financial databases\n\n6. Systemic Reforms\n- Electoral funding reforms\n- Strengthen whistleblower protection\n- Rationalize government procedures\n- Reduce discretionary powers\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Improve international financial information exchange\n- Collaborate with global anti-corruption networks\n- Track offshore financial transactions\n\nThese comprehensive strategies can help reduce black money and corruption systematically.",
